MERRY CHRISTMAS EVERYBODY!! I hope you'll all have a great day and get many great presents! I am so sorry that I don't have any presents for you like the icons you once requested... I'd make a beautiful christmas banner now...but because I still have no Photoshop, I just have this reindeer.

I am in a really christmas mood, as I am listening to christmas songs all day and sitting on my chair with a blanket on my lap... I hope you all had a good St Nicholas Day and got some candies or so! I got a lot of chocolate :) At school we had a "Nikolausturnier", where classes 5-10 play football against each other. We first had to play against the 10th classes, then against the winner class of the 9th, and of course we won ;) We kinda win every year, because we have many good players in our class (which definitely does not include me). Tomorrow the first two lessons (sports) will be cancelled *yay* But then we'll write an English test...And we don't know what will come. I hope not American history... But now the "important" stuff and me finally created our community just yesterday, means there isn't really something going on, and that really means nothing, but I thought I'd tell you, though. You know what? I finally have a journal title! *squee* It's from the song "Kirea na Kanjou" from the Noir OST 1, I really adore the lyrics of that song *swallows* And I changed some userpics...though my PC is still not fixed. But not that I miss christmas! Searching userpics I recognizied that I'm getting more and more picky when I choose one. I'm thinking about if I should create an own community for my graphics and am thinking about a name. It has to be something original... I wanted inaudible_silence, but it's just tooooo long. If somebody needs christmas music to listen to, I recommend this playlist Okay I'll finish now, have to record Prison Break ;) xoxo Juliane

I really don't have much luck in the recent past!
Guess what happened? My computer is broken! It doesn't start at all...
But that would not be too bad because my mum has a computer which she doesn't use really often, so I can be at hers (like I am now), but my whole traineeship folder is on my PC and I have to submit it tomorrow! So I called my cousin who is very good at this computer stuff and he installed my hard disk to my mums computer so that I could save the data. I wanted to print it, but my mums printer didn't work with my hard disk, we took my printer: ink empty. We put the data on my pen drive, installed my mums hard disk, tried to print with her printer,and ink was empty too! So now I'm waiting for my dad to ask if I can print it with his printer. I am at the moment not allowed to use his PC because he thinks I will corrupt it.
But that wasn't all for the day: I recognized I forgot the password for my fiction. I did one on it after I wrote on it during traineeship. Why did I! Now I am searching for a free program, I have one, but it takes ten days or something. There is a site (www.decryptum.com) but it costs 29.99$. This site can make it in one minute or something. So you can guess I am not in the best mood.
As a result, I won't be able to make any icons for who know how long. Means, no interest icons in near future, sorry.
But I hope I will still be able to post.

xoxo
Juliane

My day was not so good today... Just school. First two lessons we had chemistry. Okay, that's not bad, because our teacher seems not to know more than we do. Sometimes someone says "No, that's wrong. It's not spelled like this!" (to a chemical term) he replies: "Oh no, really? It's really not spelled like this?" Or if someone asks something or tries to explain something, it seems like he doesn't know if it's right or wrong. Maybe I have to tell that he's very new at our school, I think we are one of the first classes he teaches. Today we watched "An Inconvenient Truth". I suppose you think: What does this film have to do with chemistry? Well, that was my reaction, too! But though, I thought it was a really moving film and I nearly cried (don't know why, I was just in the mood). Then we had two hours politics (which is always kind of funny because our teacher is just crazy...so ultramotivated... I can't describe it ^^)  and then wrote our latin test. I think that was the worst latin test I have ever written! There were just 4 sentences but 77 words! And I didn't know some vocabulary and my latin teacher just didn't want to give me a tip! But I think it wouldn't have helped either if I had known it...the sentences were just to complex. Some people hadn't even written a word after half an hour... Nobody was able to translate the text... So taht was really crappy. Then we had DELF (diplome en language francais) and usually my teacher takes me home because she drives through my little hometown. But at 14.30 when the lesson ended (end's open) she said that she had to go to a conference! "Oh no! I forgot to tell you!" Arrrgh. Ah, to understand that, you have to know that my bus leaves at 14.25. Next comes 15.30. I had no money and no mobile, so I couldn't call my mum. I went to the "city" (third time this week but always just for half an hour). And so I couldn't enjoy because I already knew every shop there...
But good news, too. Yesterday (?) I got back my maths test and I have a "1+" ^^ I am good at maths ^^ I have 63 out of 61 points lol. 
And my books arrived! Can't wait to read them, but first have to read another book borrowed Monday when I went to town for half an hour after school. 

Well...why do I always write that much??

Aww I bought my a Brioche today (Lidl had french things today) 

xoxo

It's so funny, last year we did different things ( I forgot nearly everything) and now we have a different teacher and now we build things (there is no other word for "basteln", is there?). But I still have to write a biography about a mathematician. Hmm but I don't think my teacher will know him...too sad. OH NO! Sunday the very last episode of The OC will be shown. And the german title will be "Das Ende" - translated "The end". THe original title is so cool and they have such a crappy translation. Argh. But next week One Tree Hill will start! There will be many new show at German television: Heroes, Supernatural, One Tree Hill. So I think i will survive the end of The OC. I think I could make some arts... I'm back from Munich since Friday now. It was good, and we saw a lot of Munich. The whether was not best, but okay. Do you know the game Ligretto? Is it a German game? I don't know. I love this game. I played it often with two of my friend, but one friend was always winning. Always! It was so depressing ... But in the end I got better ... maybe because she was talking all the time :P
We have visited the concentration camp in Dachau... It made nearly all of us upset. I can't believe someone would do that... and Dachau was not an extermination camp! We had a guided tour and our guider told one thing I just have to tell you. There were barriers of soldiers the captured were not allowed to cross. If they did, the soldiers had to shoot them. So sometimes, a SS man took a hat off a captured and threw it across this barrier. Then he told him to take the hat. What was his choice? Being shot by a soldier or being tortured because of slighting a command. 
This makes me so sad.

Well, today was a strange day.

I never thought that I would say that, but I'm actually happy that it's raining all the time. And no, I'm not crazy. It's because on monday finally a painter will redecorate my room and if the weather was good he would have to work outside elsewhere. Yay weather I love you! But so the old wallpapers have to be removed first and that's not easy. My mother and me have worked almost all afternoon on that and then my mother fell off the ladder and fell towards the wall. You have to know, all walls in our house are made of "Rigips", that's a gypsum thing, and it's not very strong. So after the crash there was a kind of hole in my wall. Fortunately my mother was okay, one injured person in my family is enough (my father has a broken clavicle). So my room now looks quite funny but not really nice. The furniture is not where it should be and the wallpaper is lying on the floor. Tomorrow my computer desk will be moved, too. Ahh. And because of all that I have not much time.

And I have 6 hours of TV recorded on my video recorder: One episode of Numb3rs, one episode of Jericho, 2 episodes of Alias1 episdoe of Six Feet Under and one episode of McLeod's daughters. When the hell shall I watch all that stuff? Hmm oh well, I will get round to watch it.
I already saw a little bit of Six Feet Under, but it didn't finish. VOX, I hate you for the bad timing. But MTV's worse. I wanted to record Wolf's Rain, but no more than 10 minutes were recorded, the rest was "Where my dogs at?" . Arghh.

So now I am considering if I should watch a movie with my parents or watch some of the 6 hours or stay here.
Hm.

Ah, yeah, I updated my profile. It really was about time. The only thing that's still missing now is the header for my profile, but I actually have no idea what should be on the header. Someone has an idea?
Apropos header, I made a new header for my livejournal. What do you think? It's a little too dark, isn't it?

I had an eye operation on Wedneyday, because I had a stye. My eye is slowly getting better, it's not too dark anymore, just a little red. The first day after the operation was terrible, because I had bandage over my eye, just like a pirate, but bigger. I could not do anything with that, it really drove me crazy.

About tow of my six and a half weeks of holidays are passed now,. That really makes me anxious, because I did not really do anything. I mean. that's kind of the sense of holidays. But I feel they pass and pass and I don't really recognize. Okay, well, in about two weeks I will go to Berlin and I'm really looking forward to that. I hope the trip tp Berlin will be great in spite of the broken clavicle of my father.

I don't know more to write. Hm. Ah well, I stayed here xD
